]

response_parts.content:
{
  "response": [
    {
      "id": 0,
      "translated": "Welcome to ProSeka AfterTalk for the event \"Reaching Out to an Unraveling Tomorrow.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "translated": "Good evening, everyone."
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "translated": "I'm Hinata Sato, the voice of Mizuki Akiyama from Nightcord at 25:00."
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "translated": "ProSeka AfterTalk is a stream where we look back on the event while reading the fan letters you've sent in."
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "translated": "This time, we're focusing on \"Reaching Out to an Unraveling Tomorrow.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "translated": "I hope you all enjoyed the story."
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "translated": "The event actually just ended yesterday. How was it for all of you?"
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "translated": "I'd love to hear your thoughts."
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "translated": "I really hope you all had a good time with it."
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "translated": "It was a story where Mizuki really had to face the future and think about what they want to do,"
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "translated": "so I think it was quite a significant chapter."
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "translated": "For those of you who have to decide on your education or career path, there might have been parts that really hit home."
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "translated": "Also, AfterTalk got a bit of a renewal starting in April,"
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "translated": "and we've been collecting messages in advance via the official ProSeka Discord and email."
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "translated": "Thank you so much to everyone who sent one in."
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "translated": "I'll be sharing some of those messages during the show, so please look forward to that."
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "translated": "If you want to share your impressions of the event or this stream, please post using the hashtag #ProSekaAfterTalk."
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "translated": "I'm keeping an eye on the YouTube chat and I'll check the hashtag later too,"
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "translated": "so I'll try to pick up any comments that catch my eye."
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "translated": "Wow, there are so many international comments! I can barely find the Japanese ones. People are saying \"The ribbon is cute\" or \"Your hair matches Mizuki's, so cute.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "translated": "Since the stream is probably on a bit of a delay,"
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "translated": "everyone is just now noticing my hair and outfit."
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "translated": "I tried to match the card illustration for today's look—well, I always do, actually."
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "translated": "I definitely had the illustration in mind."
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "translated": "Good evening! Thank you all for joining."
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "translated": "Oh, someone said, \"The story and the new song were so good I bawled my eyes out.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "translated": "I'll talk more about the song later."
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
      "translated": "When I heard it at home, I was like, \"What is this?!\""
    },
    {
      "id": 28,
      "translated": "I was just stunned."
    },
    {
      "id": 29,
      "translated": "I really felt the incredible effort the team put into it."
    },
    {
      "id": 30,
      "translated": "Anyway, I'll save that talk for later."
    },
    {
      "id": 31,
      "translated": "So, let's dive right into the story for \"Reaching Out to an Unraveling Tomorrow.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "translated": "We've received letters about this story as well,"
    },
    {
      "id": 33,
      "translated": "so I'd like to look back on the events while reading them."
    },
    {
      "id": 34,
      "translated": "[CORNER: Fan Letter Corner] First, we have a letter from Kotori no Mama-san."
    },
    {
      "id": 35,
      "translated": "\"Hinatsu-san, Kon-Niigo!\""
    },
    {
      "id": 36,
      "translated": "Kon-Niigo!"
    },
    {
      "id": 37,
      "translated": "\"My child and I both enjoy playing ProSeka together.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 38,
      "translated": "\"Mizuki-chan's banner event was incredibly cute, funny, and moving.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 39,
      "translated": "\"Through her past experiences and her interactions with those around her,\""
    },
    {
      "id": 40,
      "translated": "\"I'm glad we got to see so many of Mizuki-chan's different feelings.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 41,
      "translated": "\"I think staying true to yourself and not giving up on what you love can be hard when you face doubts or walls.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 42,
      "translated": "\"But I believe that if you hold onto those feelings, a time will come when they are rewarded.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 43,
      "translated": "\"Just like the members of Niigo, I believe there are always people out there\""
    },
    {
      "id": 44,
      "translated": "\"who will see and accept you for who you truly are.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 45,
      "translated": "\"I really love the stories in ProSeka.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 46,
      "translated": "\"Hinatsu-san, thank you so much for always providing her voice.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 47,
      "translated": "\"I'll continue to support both Mizuki-chan and Hinatsu-san with all I've got!\""
    },
    {
      "id": 48,
      "translated": "Thank you so much, Kotori no Mama-san."
    },
    {
      "id": 49,
      "translated": "In this story, it starts with Mizuki's sister coming home from abroad to open a pop-up shop."
    },
    {
      "id": 50,
      "translated": "Mizuki wanting her sister to meet the rest of Niigo felt like a huge step forward to me."
    },
    {
      "id": 51,
      "translated": "Kanade and Mafuyu had met her before,"
    },
    {
      "id": 52,
      "translated": "but Ena finally got to meet her this time, so the relationships are really progressing."
    },
    {
      "id": 53,
      "translated": "The story moved forward in a lot of ways,"
    },
    {
      "id": 54,
      "translated": "but above all, Mizuki has so many things they love doing right now, like making videos,"
    },
    {
      "id": 55,
      "translated": "remaking clothes, visiting boutiques, and looking at makeup."
    },
    {
      "id": 56,
      "translated": "Because they have so many passions,"
    },
    {
      "id": 57,
      "translated": "I think it's amazing that they're already facing the question of what they want to aim for in the future."
    },
    {
      "id": 58,
      "translated": "When I was looking at colleges, I just thought, \"If I'm paying for this, I need to study something that gives me a practical skill,\" and I just went to tons of open houses."
    },
    {
      "id": 59,
      "translated": "My approach to finding what I liked was completely different from Mizuki's."
    },
    {
      "id": 60,
      "translated": "But I think this was a vital time for Mizuki to re-examine what they love at their own pace."
    },
    {
      "id": 61,
      "translated": "It wasn't just about the sister's pop-up shop; it was about realizing that fashion isn't just a hobby,"
    },
    {
      "id": 62,
      "translated": "but something they might want to turn into a career. That's a huge realization, and I'm just so glad Mizuki could end it with a smile."
    }
  ]
}

